00:00:11.300 --> 00:00:14.133 position:7% line:83% align:start
[Kotoko] I will stop at nothing
to win this battle.

00:00:14.167 --> 00:00:17.834 position:13% line:83% align:start
And I will pour everything
I have into these lies.

00:00:17.868 --> 00:00:20.767 position:16% line:83% align:start
The committee to conquer
Steel Lady Nanase

00:00:20.801 --> 00:00:22.300 position:24% line:89% align:start
is now in session!

00:00:26.767 --> 00:00:28.300 position:33% line:89% align:start
[Kuro grunt]

00:00:37.767 --> 00:00:41.267 position:30% line:89% align:start
[opening music]

00:02:00.367 --> 00:02:03.400 position:19% line:83% align:start
Does Steel Lady Nanase
truly exist?

00:02:03.434 --> 00:02:07.100 position:10% line:83% align:start
Or is she a fictional being,
mere rumor who was created

00:02:07.133 --> 00:02:10.000 position:30% line:83% align:start
by someone for
a specific reason?

00:02:10.033 --> 00:02:13.167 position:19% line:83% align:start
Isn't she nothing more
than an urban legend?

00:02:15.667 --> 00:02:16.300 position:30% line:89% align:start
[Kotoko] Saki.

00:02:16.334 --> 00:02:17.434 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:02:17.467 --> 00:02:19.734 position:10% line:83% align:start
If you notice any significant
change with Kuro,

00:02:19.767 --> 00:02:21.367 position:24% line:89% align:start
please let me know.

00:02:21.400 --> 00:02:22.400 position:27% line:89% align:start
Yeah, all right.

00:02:22.434 --> 00:02:24.968 position:10% line:83% align:start
He's defended himself against
Steel Lady Nanase

00:02:25.000 --> 00:02:26.901 position:7% line:89% align:start
without getting killed so far.

00:02:26.934 --> 00:02:28.267 position:16% line:89% align:start
[Kotoko] <i>Until yesterday,</i>

00:02:28.300 --> 00:02:30.734 position:33% line:83% align:start
 <i>all the talk</i>
 <i>about Steel Lady Nanase was</i>

00:02:30.767 --> 00:02:32.067 position:10% line:89% align:start
 <i>"Someone said they saw her,"</i>

00:02:32.100 --> 00:02:33.901 position:27% line:83% align:start
 <i>or "Someone said</i>
 <i>they'd been attacked."</i>

00:02:33.934 --> 00:02:35.367 position:10% line:89% align:start
 <i>Always second-hand accounts.</i>

00:02:35.400 --> 00:02:39.267 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>But as of today, there's</i>
 <i>been a significant change.</i>

00:02:39.300 --> 00:02:41.033 position:35% line:83% align:start
 <i>There was</i>
 <i>a recent incident where</i>

00:02:41.067 --> 00:02:43.200 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>a detective named Terada</i>
 <i>was killed by someone</i>

00:02:43.234 --> 00:02:46.300 position:33% line:83% align:start
 <i>believed to</i>
 <i>be Steel Lady Nanase.</i>

00:02:46.334 --> 00:02:50.200 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>The place: Makurazaka City.</i>
 <i>Time: the middle of the night.</i>

00:02:50.234 --> 00:02:52.968 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>Despite getting killed by</i>
 <i>having his face smashed in,</i>

00:02:53.000 --> 00:02:55.734 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>there were no signs that</i>
 <i>the detective resisted.</i>

00:02:55.767 --> 00:02:57.067 position:24% line:89% align:start
 <i>The cause of death</i>

00:02:57.100 --> 00:02:59.133 position:30% line:83% align:start
 <i>was announced</i>
 <i>as a blow to his face.</i>

00:02:59.167 --> 00:03:02.434 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>And so, unless something</i>
 <i>like Steel Lady Nanase</i>

00:03:02.467 --> 00:03:05.300 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>hit Terada in the face</i>
 <i>with a steel beam,</i>

00:03:05.334 --> 00:03:08.133 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>it's hard to believe anyone</i>
 <i>would die like that.</i>

00:03:10.767 --> 00:03:12.100 position:27% line:89% align:start
[anxious xxhale]

00:03:17.701 --> 00:03:18.267 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasp]

00:03:18.667 --> 00:03:20.300 position:44% line:89% align:start
 <i>No.</i>

00:03:20.334 --> 00:03:23.033 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>That's just what the killer</i>
 <i>wants you to believe.</i>

00:03:25.434 --> 00:03:27.968 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>That sort of thinking</i>
 <i>is exactly why</i>

00:03:28.000 --> 00:03:30.434 position:24% line:83% align:start
 <i>the killer needed</i>
 <i>Steel Lady Nanase.</i>

00:03:31.467 --> 00:03:33.968 position:24% line:83% align:start
 <i>In order to murder</i>
 <i>Detective Terada,</i>

00:03:34.000 --> 00:03:35.968 position:24% line:83% align:start
 <i>the killer created</i>
 <i>an urban legend and</i>

00:03:36.000 --> 00:03:39.000 position:35% line:83% align:start
 <i>called her</i>
 <i>Steel Lady Nanase.</i>

00:03:39.033 --> 00:03:40.367 position:24% line:89% align:start
They made a ghost,

00:03:40.400 --> 00:03:43.367 position:13% line:83% align:start
that has no way of existing
a suspect.

00:03:47.200 --> 00:03:50.467 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>Now, let's see how many</i>
 <i>will latch on.</i>

00:04:02.000 --> 00:04:05.434 position:21% line:83% align:start
Detective Terada was
very good at his job.

00:04:05.467 --> 00:04:08.234 position:21% line:83% align:start
He always kept an eye
on changes within the city

00:04:08.267 --> 00:04:11.567 position:13% line:83% align:start
he could almost sense when
a crime was going to happen,

00:04:11.601 --> 00:04:12.968 position:10% line:89% align:start
and he wanted to take action

00:04:13.000 --> 00:04:14.868 position:24% line:83% align:start
before the incident
got out of hand.

00:04:14.901 --> 00:04:17.033 position:41% line:83% align:start
He was
an excellent detective.

00:04:17.067 --> 00:04:20.334 position:10% line:83% align:start
That's what the killer tried
to take advantage of.

00:04:20.367 --> 00:04:22.968 position:21% line:83% align:start
A small community on
the Internet was talking about

00:04:23.000 --> 00:04:25.167 position:30% line:83% align:start
an urban legend
from Makurazaka City.

00:04:25.200 --> 00:04:27.234 position:24% line:83% align:start
By taking advantage
of that legend,

00:04:27.267 --> 00:04:29.667 position:13% line:83% align:start
they committed real crimes
and attempted

00:04:29.701 --> 00:04:33.801 position:21% line:83% align:start
even more, one crime
one right after the other.

00:04:33.834 --> 00:04:35.067 position:21% line:89% align:start
The killer dressed up

00:04:35.100 --> 00:04:37.100 position:16% line:83% align:start
the way Steel Lady Nanase
had been perceived

00:04:37.133 --> 00:04:39.467 position:24% line:83% align:start
and attacked people
night after night.

00:04:39.501 --> 00:04:42.467 position:13% line:83% align:start
They made their steel beam
from either wood or Styrofoam,

00:04:42.501 --> 00:04:45.767 position:16% line:83% align:start
and padded their chest to
help attract attention.

00:04:45.801 --> 00:04:47.501 position:16% line:83% align:start
With black paint on part
of their face,

00:04:47.534 --> 00:04:50.767 position:19% line:83% align:start
it would probably look
smashed in when seen at night.

00:04:50.801 --> 00:04:52.701 position:30% line:83% align:start
Top it off with
a large hair bow.

00:04:52.734 --> 00:04:55.100 position:10% line:83% align:start
Witnesses wouldn't have time
to think it through,

00:04:55.133 --> 00:04:58.334 position:7% line:83% align:start
so they'd just assume her face
had been smashed in.

00:04:58.367 --> 00:05:00.100 position:13% line:89% align:start
But is that even plausible?

00:05:00.133 --> 00:05:02.033 position:10% line:89% align:start
Maybe not a hundred percent.

00:05:02.067 --> 00:05:03.934 position:10% line:89% align:start
I mean, it is a lie, ya know.

00:05:03.968 --> 00:05:07.267 position:24% line:83% align:start
It just needs to be
somewhat believable.

00:05:07.300 --> 00:05:09.133 position:27% line:83% align:start
The killer waited
for statements like

00:05:09.167 --> 00:05:11.968 position:24% line:83% align:start
"I was attacked by
Steel Lady Nanase" to spread,

00:05:12.000 --> 00:05:13.868 position:10% line:89% align:start
not just as an online rumor,

00:05:13.901 --> 00:05:15.968 position:16% line:83% align:start
but in real reports taken
to the police.

00:05:16.000 --> 00:05:19.300 position:7% line:83% align:start
But the police didn't initially
take these stories seriously.

00:05:19.334 --> 00:05:21.734 position:21% line:83% align:start
I'm sure many victims
had second thoughts

00:05:21.767 --> 00:05:23.367 position:19% line:89% align:start
about filing a report.

00:05:23.400 --> 00:05:26.801 position:5% line:83% align:start
But if incidents like that began
occurring all over the city,

00:05:26.834 --> 00:05:28.167 position:7% line:89% align:start
wouldn't a good detective think

00:05:28.200 --> 00:05:30.968 position:19% line:83% align:start
something was going on
and take action?

00:05:31.000 --> 00:05:33.133 position:16% line:83% align:start
[Terada] <i>Someone could be</i>
 <i>acting like a monster</i>

00:05:33.167 --> 00:05:36.968 position:21% line:83% align:start
 <i>from an urban legend</i>
 <i>as part of a much larger plot.</i>

00:05:37.000 --> 00:05:39.000 position:24% line:83% align:start
 <i>And with the work</i>
 <i>they're putting in,</i>

00:05:39.033 --> 00:05:41.100 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>it can't be dismissed</i>
 <i>as a mere prank.</i>

00:05:41.133 --> 00:05:44.267 position:21% line:83% align:start
 <i>They might actually</i>
 <i>be planning some crime.</i>

00:05:44.300 --> 00:05:46.100 position:21% line:83% align:start
[Kotoko] That thought
crossed his mind,

00:05:46.133 --> 00:05:48.300 position:16% line:83% align:start
so he began investigating
on his own.

00:05:48.334 --> 00:05:51.868 position:13% line:83% align:start
This is the exact response
that the killer wanted.

00:05:51.901 --> 00:05:54.367 position:24% line:83% align:start
If Detective Terada
started investigating

00:05:54.400 --> 00:05:56.133 position:10% line:89% align:start
Steel Lady Nanase by himself,

00:05:56.167 --> 00:05:59.167 position:16% line:83% align:start
they'd easily be able to
get the detective alone.

00:05:59.200 --> 00:06:01.367 position:16% line:83% align:start
Thus, the killer was able
to create a time frame

00:06:01.400 --> 00:06:04.434 position:19% line:83% align:start
where the accomplished
detective would be on his own.

00:06:06.501 --> 00:06:09.067 position:35% line:83% align:start
[Anonymous]
 <i>Too long. Didn't read this.</i>

00:06:09.100 --> 00:06:10.834 position:35% line:83% align:start
[Anonymous]
 <i>What're you basing this on?</i>

00:06:10.868 --> 00:06:12.367 position:21% line:83% align:start
[Anon] <i>But Steel Lady</i>
 <i>Nanase is real!</i>

00:06:12.400 --> 00:06:14.067 position:21% line:83% align:start
[Anonymous] <i>The only</i>
 <i>logical explanation is that</i>

00:06:14.100 --> 00:06:16.067 position:19% line:89% align:start
 <i>it really was a ghost.</i>

00:06:17.033 --> 00:06:19.367 position:41% line:83% align:start
[Anon]
 <i>I say let's hear them out.</i>

00:06:19.400 --> 00:06:21.634 position:10% line:83% align:start
[Anonymous] <i>I'm sure there's</i>
 <i>gotta be some people here</i>

00:06:21.667 --> 00:06:23.334 position:10% line:89% align:start
 <i>who don't believe in ghosts.</i>

00:06:24.601 --> 00:06:25.968 position:13% line:89% align:start
The killer, at that point,

00:06:26.000 --> 00:06:28.200 position:27% line:83% align:start
made contact with
the detective.

00:06:31.501 --> 00:06:32.434 position:30% line:89% align:start
This is Terada.

00:06:32.467 --> 00:06:33.634 position:24% line:89% align:start
[killer] <i>Detective!</i>

00:06:33.667 --> 00:06:36.267 position:21% line:83% align:start
 <i>I was just attacked</i>
 <i>by Steel Lady Nanase!</i>

00:06:36.300 --> 00:06:37.100 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasp]

00:06:37.133 --> 00:06:38.534 position:13% line:89% align:start
 <i>She ended up running off,</i>

00:06:38.567 --> 00:06:41.133 position:30% line:83% align:start
but she dropped
her weapon and bow.

00:06:41.167 --> 00:06:43.067 position:27% line:83% align:start
I think they left
some footprints behind

00:06:43.100 --> 00:06:44.367 position:27% line:83% align:start
that you may want
to check out,

00:06:44.400 --> 00:06:46.968 position:16% line:83% align:start
But if I'm wrong, I don't
want to look like a fool,

00:06:47.000 --> 00:06:48.801 position:21% line:89% align:start
so please come alone.

00:06:48.834 --> 00:06:50.534 position:10% line:83% align:start
[Kotoko] That's could be all
it took for Detective Terada

00:06:50.567 --> 00:06:53.968 position:30% line:83% align:start
to rush over to
the call on his own.

00:06:54.000 --> 00:06:55.868 position:33% line:83% align:start
And the place
he was summoned to

00:06:55.901 --> 00:06:57.701 position:30% line:83% align:start
ended up being
the scene of the crime,

00:06:57.734 --> 00:06:59.901 position:13% line:89% align:start
the abandoned gas station.

00:06:59.934 --> 00:07:01.834 position:24% line:83% align:start
If he'd been called
like that,

00:07:01.868 --> 00:07:03.834 position:16% line:83% align:start
Detective Terada might've
really gone

00:07:03.868 --> 00:07:05.234 position:10% line:89% align:start
to an abandoned gas station.

00:07:06.400 --> 00:07:08.901 position:13% line:83% align:start
[Kotoko] In the time before
Detective Terada showed up,

00:07:08.934 --> 00:07:13.667 position:7% line:83% align:start
the killer rigged a few things
at the abandoned gas station.

00:07:13.701 --> 00:07:14.834 position:21% line:89% align:start
First, they suspended

00:07:14.868 --> 00:07:16.367 position:24% line:83% align:start
a massive pendulum
from the roof,

00:07:16.400 --> 00:07:19.067 position:19% line:83% align:start
by attaching a rope to
a hook on the edge

00:07:19.100 --> 00:07:21.367 position:21% line:83% align:start
and secured a weight
at the bottom.

00:07:22.734 --> 00:07:23.934 position:21% line:83% align:start
The weight had to be
heavy enough

00:07:23.968 --> 00:07:25.234 position:27% line:89% align:start
and dense enough,

00:07:25.267 --> 00:07:27.033 position:24% line:83% align:start
that it could crack
someone's cranium open

00:07:27.067 --> 00:07:28.400 position:21% line:89% align:start
with a single swing.

00:07:29.434 --> 00:07:32.067 position:19% line:83% align:start
The angle of its swing
needed to be precise,

00:07:32.100 --> 00:07:34.267 position:24% line:83% align:start
and calculated for
the Detective's height,

00:07:34.300 --> 00:07:37.033 position:21% line:83% align:start
which the killer had
previously researched.

00:07:38.167 --> 00:07:40.033 position:27% line:83% align:start
Once they had all
that finished,

00:07:40.067 --> 00:07:42.100 position:21% line:83% align:start
the killer would keep
the rope extended

00:07:42.133 --> 00:07:44.868 position:10% line:83% align:start
take the end of the pendulum
that had the weight on it,

00:07:44.901 --> 00:07:46.834 position:24% line:83% align:start
and set the weight
on the other hook

00:07:46.868 --> 00:07:48.567 position:7% line:89% align:start
set up further along the roof.

00:07:49.801 --> 00:07:52.467 position:7% line:83% align:start
However, this hook was attached
to a mechanism that

00:07:52.501 --> 00:07:56.200 position:13% line:83% align:start
could undo it at any time,
by remote control.

00:07:57.868 --> 00:07:59.501 position:30% line:83% align:start
Once that hook
was disengaged,

00:07:59.534 --> 00:08:03.801 position:10% line:83% align:start
the weight would come flying
down at incredible speed.

00:08:03.834 --> 00:08:07.100 position:5% line:83% align:start
This is an insane amount of work
just to kill one person.

00:08:09.400 --> 00:08:11.367 position:16% line:83% align:start
The killer would have to
get Detective Terada

00:08:11.400 --> 00:08:14.767 position:16% line:83% align:start
to stand in the spot they
had previously chosen.

00:08:14.801 --> 00:08:16.868 position:27% line:83% align:start
But that wouldn't
be difficult.

00:08:16.901 --> 00:08:18.133 position:13% line:89% align:start
The killer could have held

00:08:18.167 --> 00:08:20.901 position:24% line:83% align:start
an item of interest
to Detective Terada.

00:08:20.934 --> 00:08:22.634 position:24% line:83% align:start
If they waited with
that in hand

00:08:22.667 --> 00:08:23.968 position:10% line:89% align:start
at the abandoned gas station,

00:08:24.000 --> 00:08:26.434 position:19% line:83% align:start
Detective Terada would
undoubtedly stop his car

00:08:26.467 --> 00:08:27.434 position:27% line:89% align:start
near the killer.

00:08:27.467 --> 00:08:29.400 position:16% line:83% align:start
Detective! Here's the bow
that she dropped.

00:08:29.434 --> 00:08:33.501 position:21% line:83% align:start
And those footprints
are just over there.

00:08:33.534 --> 00:08:35.300 position:27% line:83% align:start
It's a bit dark,
so I'll go on ahead

00:08:35.334 --> 00:08:37.801 position:19% line:83% align:start
and turn on some lights
so that you don't trip.

00:08:37.834 --> 00:08:39.300 position:35% line:83% align:start
Wait here.
I'll be right back.

00:08:39.334 --> 00:08:40.467 position:44% line:89% align:start
Sure.

00:08:40.501 --> 00:08:42.234 position:10% line:83% align:start
[Kotoko] And that's probably
all it took to get

00:08:42.267 --> 00:08:45.400 position:16% line:83% align:start
Detective Terada to stand
where the killer wanted him to.

00:08:45.434 --> 00:08:48.367 position:7% line:83% align:start
At that moment, the killer used
the remote control,

00:08:48.400 --> 00:08:51.267 position:24% line:83% align:start
releasing the hook
that held the weight.

00:08:53.267 --> 00:08:55.434 position:16% line:83% align:start
The weight being held by
the rope would act

00:08:55.467 --> 00:08:56.534 position:30% line:89% align:start
as a pendulum,

00:08:56.567 --> 00:08:59.667 position:16% line:83% align:start
swinging across the dark,
abandoned gas station

00:08:59.701 --> 00:09:01.334 position:27% line:83% align:start
to split his head
with one blow,

00:09:01.367 --> 00:09:04.634 position:7% line:83% align:start
as Detective Terada unknowingly
stood in its path.

00:09:04.667 --> 00:09:07.267 position:16% line:83% align:start
There were no residences
near the crime scene,

00:09:07.300 --> 00:09:09.100 position:16% line:89% align:start
and cars rarely drove by,

00:09:09.133 --> 00:09:12.534 position:13% line:83% align:start
so no one would've noticed
the rigged pendulum above.

00:09:12.567 --> 00:09:15.968 position:13% line:83% align:start
The Detective wouldn't see
the pendulum set up to kill him

00:09:16.000 --> 00:09:18.267 position:7% line:89% align:start
until it was already too late.

00:09:19.434 --> 00:09:20.634 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasp]

00:09:20.667 --> 00:09:21.901 position:35% line:89% align:start
Yes, I see!

00:09:21.934 --> 00:09:24.501 position:30% line:83% align:start
Now that better
explains the mystery.

00:09:24.534 --> 00:09:27.167 position:21% line:83% align:start
This is how a strong,
and highly skilled detective,

00:09:27.200 --> 00:09:31.000 position:10% line:83% align:start
could be dispatched so easily
without signs of a struggle.

00:09:31.033 --> 00:09:32.968 position:27% line:83% align:start
There was no way
he could have predicted

00:09:33.000 --> 00:09:34.701 position:21% line:83% align:start
that he'd be attacked
by a pendulum,

00:09:34.734 --> 00:09:35.834 position:19% line:89% align:start
cracking his head open,

00:09:35.868 --> 00:09:38.067 position:27% line:83% align:start
without a chance
to defend himself.

00:09:38.100 --> 00:09:40.000 position:30% line:83% align:start
After murdering
Detective Terada,

00:09:40.033 --> 00:09:41.901 position:30% line:83% align:start
the killer puts
their setup away.

00:09:41.934 --> 00:09:43.901 position:21% line:83% align:start
They remove any trace
of being there

00:09:43.934 --> 00:09:45.334 position:30% line:89% align:start
flee the scene.

00:09:46.200 --> 00:09:48.200 position:13% line:83% align:start
All that's left after that
is to burn

00:09:48.234 --> 00:09:50.367 position:21% line:83% align:start
the costume they used
as Steel Lady Nanase,

